____________________________________________________________</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1043<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/6/01 10:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> Actually Veladorn you are mistaken.  All casters have the same level limits, all casters use the same formula.  To my knowledge this system has always been in place, at least since June of 99 when I started the game, although it probably wasn't there in beta and might not have been in release.  My magician friend can hit things more than 7 levels over his head at level 48, its all classes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 492<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/7/01 12:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 6 level hard cap on spell damage?</span><hr size=1> Wizards have a slight edge, really we do.<br>
<br>
Find a wizard and a mage same level (mid 30s at least) Find the deepest red mob a wiz can cast on then let the mage try it.  Mage won't be able to touch it with spells.<br>
<br>
This is really in the game Grim.  When I was lower level I tested it myself in sol B.<br>
<br>
 <p>Valas Defai<BR>
